## New Tools
The following items can be selected as tool proficiencies in addition to the options presented in Chapter 5 of the Player's Handbook.

***Engineer's tools.*** This set of artisan's tools allows you to craft and maintain a wide variety of marvels, from firearms and explosives to gadgets and constructs. <!-- ***Gunsmith's tools.*** These artisan's tools are used not only to craft firearms and their ammunition, but explosives such as dynamite and grenades. --> 

***Enchanter's supplies.*** These artisan's tools are used to inspect and manipulate magic items and spells.

***Hearthstone card set.*** This game pits two opponents against each other using decks of thirty constructed by each player pulled from thousands of potential cards. Each card set comes with a protective box that includes dice, the rule book, and a catalog of official cards.

***Pandaren jihui board.*** This board game is designed to allow for both players to arrive at a satisfying conclusion and thus is a good way to pass the time peacefully.

***Suturing kit.*** This set of needles, thread, and other tools is used to stitch together flesh. The usage of this kit varies from stapling together large wounds to creating taxidermy. Corporeal undead such as the forsaken have made use of these kits to repair and replace their rotting flesh and limbs. Proficiency with this kit allows you to add your proficiency bonus to any ability checks you make to stitch flesh or even simpler materials such as cloth or leather.

***War Drums.*** **[The large orc drums carried on the back of a kodo.]**

\pagebreak

> #### Variant: Industrial Revolution
> The table of prices for adventuring gear in the Player's Handbook is designed for a typical fantasy setting. Azeroth is not a typical fantasy setting. Between the gnomes, dwarves, and goblins, a certain level of technological advancement and a low level of industry has emerged. This results in certain items that would normally be expensive to be cheaper to acquire. When using this variant rule, follow the below guidelines:
> - Items made primarily of paper or ink cost half as much.
> - Items made of intricate or precision metalwork, such as a signet ring or timepiece, are ten times cheaper.
> - Items made of complex glasswork, such as a magnifying glass or spyglass, are twenty times cheaper.
> - Items that have significant game effects, such as plate armor or alchemist's fire, should not have their price adjusted.



### Expanded Tool Descriptions
Below are expanded descriptions of potential uses of the new tools, following the rules set forth in Chapter 2 of Xanathar's Guide to Everything.

#### Air Vehicles
Proficiency with air vehicles covers both powered flight options, from the single-pilot gyrocopter to the mighty gunship, and unpowered vehicles, such as simple gliders and hot air balloons. Proficiency with these vehicles also includes the knowledge needed to handle them, such as being able to identify weather patterns and potential landing sites, as well as how to repair and maintain their vehicles.

***Arcana.*** When you study a magic vehicle, this tool proficiency aids you in uncovering lore or determining how the vehicle operates.

***Investigation, Perception.*** When you inspect a vehicle for clues or hidden information, your proficiency aids you in noticing things that others might miss.

***Nature.*** When you try to determine future weather conditions such as a potential rainstorm, you can add your proficiency bonus to the check.

***Vehicle Handling.*** When piloting a vehicle, you can apply your proficiency bonus to the vehicle’s AC and saving throws.

##### Air Vehicles
Activity                            | DC
------------------------------------|----
Navigate rough air currents         | 10
Assess a vehicle's condition        | 15
Take a tight corner at high speed   | 20

#### Enchanter's Supplies
These supplies are used to inspect and manipulate magic items and spells.

***Components.*** A set of enchanter's supplies includes several pouches of magic-infused powders and crystal shards, as well as small brushes, tweezers, a runed metal rod, and a pair of crystal lenses.

***Arcana.*** Proficiency with enchanter's supplies allows you to unlock more information on Arcana checks involving magic items.

***Investigation.*** When you inspect or research a magic item, your proficiency with enchanter's supplies grants additional insight.

***Detect Magic.*** By closely inspecting an item for 10 minutes, your proficiency with enchanter's supplies allows you to duplicate the effects of the *identify* spell. By using your enchanter's supplies and spending 1 minute walking around an area with no more than a 30 foot radius, you can instantaneously identify any magical auras, as the *detect magic* spell.

##### Enchanter's Supplies
Activity                                | DC
----------------------------------------|-----
Determine whether an item is magical    | 10
Disable a magical trap                  | Varies

\pagebreak

#### Engineer's Tools
A set of engineer's tools allows you to craft and maintain a wide variety of marvels, from firearms and explosives to gadgets and constructs.

***Components.*** Engineer's tools come in a metal box with compartments containing a plethora of springs, gears, wires, powders, and other parts, as well as a variety of hammers, screwdrivers, and wrenches.

***Arcana, History.*** Your expertise lends you additional insight into firearms, explosives, and mechanical constructs or devices.

***Investigation, Perception.*** You can spot clues and make deductions that others might overlook when firearms, explosives, or mechanical constructs or devices are involved in an investigation.

***Repair.*** As part of a short rest, you can repair a single damaged firearm. With sufficient spare parts, you can restore 10 hit points to a mechanical construct or device for each hour of work.

***Mechanical Crafting.*** You can use this tool proficiency to create mechanical items. A character can spend money to collect raw materials, which weigh 1 pound for every 50 gp spent. The GM can allow a character to make a check using the indicated skill with advantage. As part of a long rest, you can use engineer's tools to make twenty firearm bullets or one stick of dynamite, electric lantern, flashlight, grenade, music box, scope, or spyglass. Subtract half the value of the created item from the total gp worth of raw materials you are carrying.

##### Engineer's Tools
Activity                                | DC
----------------------------------------|-----
Craft bullets using an unusual material | 15
Disarm an explosive                     | Varies

#### Fishing Tackle

Adventuring gear
1 gp, 4 lb.
This kit includes a wooden rod, silken line, corkwood bobbers, steel hooks, lead sinkers, velvet lures, and narrow netting.

---

Adventuring gear, 1 sp

Basic Fishing Equipment includes a pole, a line, a hook, and either a lure or some bait.

Fishing is a popular pastime in Wildspace and the Astral Sea, though this activity isn't possible aboard a ship that is moving faster than its flying speed. At the end of each hour spent fishing, a character can make a DC 15 Wisdom (Survival) check. A failed check indicates no fish is caught during that hour. On a successful check, roll a d10 and consult the Fishing table to determine the catch.

##### Fishing
|&nbsp; d10 |&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;| Catch |
|:---:|-|---|
| 1–2 || Tiny, inedible fish (a creature that consumes it is poisoned for 1 hour) |
| 3–5 || Tiny, edible fish (feeds one person) |
| 6–8 || Small, edible fish (feeds up to four people) |
| 9   || Hostile murloc fisherman (carrying enough fish to feed up to twelve people) <br/> [ORIGINAL: **space eel**](https://5e.tools/bestiary.html#space%20eel_bam) (see *Boo's Astral Menagerie*; feeds up to twelve people) |
| 10  || Hostile (crocolisk? naga? markrura?) <br/> [ORIGINAL: **gray scavver**](https://5e.tools/bestiary.html#gray%20scavver_bam) (see *Boo's Astral Menagerie*; feeds up to twenty people), some other creature of the DM's choosing, or an Tiny object of the DM's choosing |

#### Suturing Kit
Originally a tool used by surgeons to sew together gaping wounds or taxidermists to preserve a beloved animal companion, these tools have come into greater prominence with the rise of the living dead.

***Components.*** A suturing kit contains a variety of needles, surgical blades, and threads, as well as small jars of preservatives, antiseptics, and painkillers.

***Medicine.*** Your practice at stitching flesh gives you insight into how to best treat large wounds.

***Perception.*** Your familiarity with the patterns of flesh lets you better notice faded scars and surgical marks.

***Rapid Stabilize.*** When using a healer's kit to stabilize a creature, you can do so as a bonus action.

***Repair Undead.*** You can use your kit to attach or reattach flesh and limbs to corporeal undead, provided that the new material is similar to the missing body part. This may take anywhere from a few minutes to several hours.

##### Suturing Kit
Activity                                | DC
----------------------------------------|-----
Stitch or patch skin, cloth, or leather | 10
Reattach limb                           | 15
Attach new limb in place of missing one | 20

