### Variant Rule: Intoxication
**[A variant ruleset for intoxication? Between dwarves, pandaren, and Brewfest, alcohol is more of a thing for WoW than other places. So a minor ruleset for alcohol and inebriation might not be amiss.]**

Examples:
- [One](https://www.reddit.com/r/DnD/comments/4o1p6m/5e_drinking_rules/)
- [Two](https://www.gmbinder.com/share/-LwW9VsLu8w6Fe475DMj)

1+CON_SCORE+RACIAL_MODIFIER

Racial modifier is from +2 to -2, based on the race's size and Con bonus, with humans being +0. Gnomes get drunk a lot faster than a tauren would, after all.

##### Alcohol Strengths
